The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Dax switches to new strategy 

 ALOKANANDA GHOSH

 Calcutta, Sept. 4: Dax Networks will focus on core products like switches, routers and security products to enter new markets.

 The Chennai-based networking company will concentrate on key verticals of telecom, enterprises, government, small units, banks and financial institutions.

 Dax will, however, continue to offer its entire range of products. Dax Networks country manager K. Surendar said, We have adopted a towards the core strategy wherein we are focusing on key products that generate more revenues because of high demand. We are also strengthening our product portfolio to meet the requirements of both existing and upgraded networks.

 Routers and switches make up around 40 per cent of the networking market, while security products form 50 per cent. All other products make up for the remaining 10 per cent. A router is a device that directs traffic from one point to another in a local area network or the Internet.

 The newer versions of routers are capable of distinguishing different types of traffic ? voice, data, fax or video ? and direct it to the desired location. 




